<augment_code_snippet path="src/modules/Products/products.controller.js" mode="EXCERPT">
```javascript
// Extract public ID from Cloudinary URL for deletion
let cloudinaryPublicId = null;
try {
 const urlParts = deletedImageInfo.imageUrl.split('/');
 const uploadIndex = urlParts.indexOf('upload');
 if (uploadIndex !== -1 && uploadIndex + 2 < urlParts.length) {
 const pathWithExtension = urlParts.slice(uploadIndex + 2).join('/');
 cloudinaryPublicId = pathWithExtension.replace(/\.[^/.]+$/, '');
 }
} catch (urlParseError) {
 console.warn('Could not parse Cloudinary URL for deletion:', urlParseError.message);
}
```
</augment_code_snippet>

1. **Automatic URL Parsing**: Extracts public ID from Cloudinary URLs
2. **Dual Deletion**: Removes from both database and Cloudinary
3. **Graceful Degradation**: Database operation succeeds even if Cloudinary fails
4. **Status Reporting**: Returns whether Cloudinary deletion was successful

